title: jemalloc(?) bug while iterating std::io::Lines
body:
I am using the following code to read from a file and print it line by line:

``` rust
use machine_state::OpCode;
use std::io::prelude::*;
use std::io::BufReader;
use std::fs::File;
use std::path::Path;

pub fn parse(path_string: &String) {
   let path = Path::new(path_string);
    let mut file = match File::open(path) {
        Ok(file) => file,
        Err(..)  => panic!("room"),
    };
    let mut reader = BufReader::new(&file);
    let s = &mut String::new();
    for line in reader.lines() {
        match line {
            Ok(x) => println!("OK!: {}", x),
            Err(x) => println!("Err: {}", x),
        }
    }
}
```

This function is called at the beginning of [this code](https://github.com/pczora/olderon/blob/5e92e7ff20863522833a05f9bf4befc177d78aea/src/main.rs) and should read a file and print it line by line. I ran the code via `cargo run /tmp/in.txt`, where `/tmp/in.txt` is a text file containing

```
hello 1
hello 2
```

I expect the output to be those to lines, instead, this is printed:
